    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d0349f17_8a21edba",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrContext.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 445,
      "author": {
        "id": 5230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T19:18:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well, in the flushState version we will have had to have made all the intermediate flushing decisions ahead of time, so I think we will need it. That said the compatibility enforcement allows the final SkSurface to have greater limits - it just can have less resources.\n\nWe could just not enforce compatibility at all on the dest SkSurface (just blow past the budget) but I think we would still want these here to be able to add intermediate flushes.",
      "parentUuid": "1e8c8862_5c7f0d48",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 442,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 445,
        "endChar": 87
      },
      "revId": "1a90e58fa2525c496034cad1d6fc40e1777a7b8e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "66694067_770f6545",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrContext.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 445,
      "author": {
        "id": 5230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T19:22:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ha - I fell behind on the comments. In the opList world we are not splitting the opLists based on these limits. For the opList implementation I intend to add partial flushing of opLists at flush time.\n\nIn the flushState world I think we will need to actually run the allocation algorithm to insert the intermediate flushes.",
      "parentUuid": "d0349f17_8a21edba",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 442,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 445,
        "endChar": 87
      },
      "revId": "1a90e58fa2525c496034cad1d6fc40e1777a7b8e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d265da66_202d6568",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrContext.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 445,
      "author": {
        "id": 5230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T19:25:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The contract is already a bit squishy btw. If they replay us into a GrContext that has compatible limits but is filled with textures locked in VRAM, we\u0027re going to go overbudget.\n\nThe promise is more, if you replay this DDL into a GrContext that has no memory consumed already and has compatible limits then we will only every go over budget for a single draw.",
      "parentUuid": "66694067_770f6545",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 442,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 445,
        "endChar": 87
      },
      "revId": "1a90e58fa2525c496034cad1d6fc40e1777a7b8e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "16f351d9_3db50195",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrContext.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 445,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T19:29:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Got it. Maybe Greg\u0027s suggestion makes sense... temporarily override the the budget during replay.\n\nA long time ago we tried to remove the Count part of the budget and failed because of a perf issue in a really old Mac GL driver that got triggered by gradient textures. This is before we had analytic gradients and before atlasing. Maybe we could go with just a bytes here and work towards removing the count from GrContext?",
      "parentUuid": "d0349f17_8a21edba",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 442,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 445,
        "endChar": 87
      },
      "revId": "1a90e58fa2525c496034cad1d6fc40e1777a7b8e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c31e4315_e9b690db",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrContext.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 458,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T19:02:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Should we take a GrBackendTexture and ignore its texture id? My concern is around whether we will want to know the exact texture format.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 456,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 458,
        "endChar": 59
      },
      "revId": "1a90e58fa2525c496034cad1d6fc40e1777a7b8e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c7747dca_cff81d44",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrContext.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 458,
      "author": {
        "id": 5230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T19:18:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well, in an earlier iteration I explicitly passed in the width/height/pixelConfig and colorSpace but I switched to an SkImageInfo since I know you\u0027re trying to hide pixelConfig. But I think pixelConfig is what we want at this level of the API.",
      "parentUuid": "c31e4315_e9b690db",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 456,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 458,
        "endChar": 59
      },
      "revId": "1a90e58fa2525c496034cad1d6fc40e1777a7b8e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1e3b0b96_16bc2d93",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrContext.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 458,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T19:29:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In SkSurface/SkImage we infer the pixel config from a GrBackendTexture/GrRenderTarget\u0027s texture format. I was thinking we could do the same thing here.\n\nI\u0027m not crazy about passing a GrGLTextureInfo, for instance, where we ignore the ID. Esp. because GrGLFramebufferInfo has no invalid value for fFBOID. But maybe we can live with it.\n\nI\u0027m not exactly sure how to solve this... decompose Gr[GL|Vk].*Info to? Make a GrBackendFormat that wraps either a GLenum or a VkFormat? In GL do we also want to see the target enum?",
      "parentUuid": "c7747dca_cff81d44",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 456,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 458,
        "endChar": 59
      },
